parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the airbag is designed to absorb the impact and reduce the force of the crash on the occupants.
symptoms: The airbag does not deploy in a crash
even when the vehicle is involved in a severe impact
resulting in injuries to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The airbag deploys without a crash or impact
causing sudden and unexpected inflation
which can startle the driver and cause loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper deployment of the airbag can cause injuries, as the airbag may not deploy correctly or may deploy with excessive force.
symptoms: The airbag deploys violently
causing injuries
or deploys slowly
reducing its effectiveness in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when braking, leading to loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: Vibrations or shaking when braking
brake pedal goes to the floor
brake pedal vibrates
front end vibrates vigorously while braking
stopping several feet past the point where the brakes were applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of underrated tires can cause brake overheating, leading to warped brake rotors, which can result in loss of braking performance and increased stopping distance.
symptoms: Brake rotors overheated and cracked
tires wobbled and became unstable after 15-20 minutes of driving
brake rotors had to be replaced multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the vehicle to zigzag or lose control when braking, leading to accidents.
symptoms: ABS brake light comes on
pedal goes to the floor
car zigzags in the back and eventually stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Interference with Brake Operation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interference of the electrical system with brake operation can cause the headlights to flicker and dim, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights flicker and dim when engaging brakes or turning on cabin electrical devices
poor idling attributed to low voltage to idle speed motor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The warping of the rear brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pulsate when braking, leading to loss of control and increased stopping distance.
symptoms: Rear brake rotors out of round
causing pulsation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle remains in lower gears
runs at higher RPMs than normal
transmission revs up to excessive RPMs at normal speed
transmission slips from drive to neutral gear
transmission failure at low mileage (e.g.
000 miles).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission slips from drive to neutral gear
transmission revs up to excessive RPMs at normal speed
transmission failure at low mileage (e.g.
000 miles).
